{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "648b5a6c417cc3fb48d678a8", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76b2c52ffa3c944600df"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eba2"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "62c481f001514d218a7934d3", "title": "JEE Main 2022 (25 Jun Shift 1)", "isVisible": true}], "type": "singleCorrect", "level": 1, "approximateTimeRequired": 120, "question": {"text": "A light wave travelling linearly in a medium of dielectric constant <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn></math>, incidents on the horizontal interface separating medium with air. The angle of incidence for which the total intensity of incident wave will be reflected back into the same medium will be :<br />(Given : relative permeability of medium <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>&#956;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">r</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>)", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "Cspnm", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math>", "isCorrect": false, "image": null}, {"id": "YmceN", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>20</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math>", "isCorrect": false, "image": null}, {"id": "BzKaO", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>30</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math>", "isCorrect": false, "image": null}, {"id": "QQNGS", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>60</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math>", "isCorrect": true, "image": null}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "<p>Relative refractive index is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#956;</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><msub><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>r</mi></msub><msub><mi>&#949;</mi><mi>r</mi></msub></msqrt><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>4</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>1</mn></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math></p><p>Now, for complete reflection,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><msub><mi>&#952;</mi><mi>c</mi></msub></math>, where,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>&#952;</mi><mi>c</mi></msub></math>&nbsp;is critical angle.</p><p>Now, critical angle is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><msub><mi>&#952;</mi><mi>c</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>&#956;</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>&#952;</mi><mi>c</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>&#952;</mi><mi>c</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>30</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math></p><p>So, the angle of incidence for which the total intensity of incident wave will be reflected back into the same medium is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><mn>30</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math>&nbsp;i.e.,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>60</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math>.</p>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "questionLabels": [], "masterId": "MOGJMPYQ65479589", "source": "EM", "bucket": "Must Do Ques (JEE Main) - Any Difficulty", "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "category": null, "microConcepts": [], "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "isRemoved": false, "cpyqbSubjects": ["61bb58181213731910ea0b70", "61c055eae8ce0dc8a5c62d33", "616057750283de43c87e3e1b", "61964fe0a5a5260118868021", "61964f81a5a526011886801d", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625b", "616057920283de43c87e3e1e", "615f0c729476412f48314dab", "61a8a2c2e8ce0dc8a5c62d2d", "629105adee9e3ae00d63352b", "629f385f263330a77be9fa7d", "616056cd0283de43c87e3e1